      "description": "Implement SuperHuman-Inspired Command Palette & Keyboard Shortcut System\n\nIntroduce a fast, keyboard-driven command palette modeled on SuperHuman's interaction paradigm, giving power users the ability to navigate the entire Krisp hub without lifting their hands from the keyboard.\n\nRequirements:\n\nCommand Palette UI\n- Trigger the palette globally with Cmd+K (Mac) / Ctrl+K (Windows/Linux) from any view\n- Render a centered modal overlay with a fuzzy-search input at the top and a scrollable results list below\n- Show contextual command groups (e.g., Navigation, Kanban, Email, Meetings, Open Brain, Settings) with visual section dividers\n- Display each result with an icon, label, keyboard shortcut hint (if one exists), and a secondary description line\n- Highlight matched characters in the search results to reinforce fuzzy-match feedback\n- Dismiss on Escape or click-outside; maintain focus trap while open\n- Animate open/close with a subtle fade+scale transition consistent with the existing dark mode color system tokens\n\nKeyboard Shortcut Coverage\n- Navigation: jump to Kanban board, Inbox, Meetings, Open Brain, and Settings views without the palette (direct hotkeys)\n- Kanban: create new card (C), open search (/ or S), cycle through columns (Tab / Shift+Tab), archive selected card, change priority\n- Email: compose new message, mark as read/unread, archive, move to next/previous thread (J/K SuperHuman-style)\n- Meetings: open most recent meeting, trigger AI semantic search\n- Open Brain: open quick-capture input, trigger semantic memory search\n- Global: toggle dark/light mode, open help/shortcut reference sheet (?)\n\nShortcut Registry & Discoverability\n- Maintain a centralized shortcut registry (TypeScript constant or config file) as the single source of truth for all bindings so shortcuts defined here automatically populate the palette and the reference sheet\n- Build a full shortcut reference sheet rendered at ? or via the palette with \"Show all shortcuts\", organized by category with visual keyboard glyphs (⌘, ⇧, ⌃, ⌥)\n\nConflict Prevention & Accessibility\n- Suppress shortcuts when focus is inside a text input, textarea, Markdown editor (@uiw/react-md-editor), or modal form to avoid accidental triggers\n- Respect existing @dnd-kit drag interactions — ensure no shortcut conflicts with drag-and-drop keyboard controls\n- Support remappable bindings stored in user preferences (database-backed), surfaced through a settings panel\n- All palette interactions must be fully navigable with arrow keys and Enter/Space; ensure ARIA roles (role=\"dialog\", role=\"listbox\", aria-activedescendant) are correct\n\nTechnical Implementation Notes\n- Implement shortcut listening via a custom useKeyboardShortcut hook wrapping native keydown listeners, with automatic cleanup on unmount\n- Integrate with TanStack React Query so palette actions that mutate data (e.g., create card, archive email) reuse existing query/mutation hooks and keep the cache consistent\n- Lazy-load the palette component so it does not contribute to initial bundle size\n- Consider using cmdk (the headless command menu primitive used by Vercel, Linear, etc.) as the palette foundation to avoid rebuilding focus management and accessibility from scratch\n\nEdge Cases to Consider\n- Palette opened while a drag-and-drop operation is in progress\n- Shortcut fired while an async action (e.g., AI search) is already in-flight\n- User navigates to a view that does not exist yet (graceful no-op or toast)\n- Very long command lists — ensure virtual scrolling or a reasonable result cap (e.g., top 8–10 results) keeps the palette feeling instant",
