  "summary": "## Summary: Implement SuperHuman-Inspired Command Palette & Keyboard Shortcut System\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- **Centralized Shortcut Registry**: Created `lib/shortcuts/registry.ts` as the single source of truth for all keyboard bindings. Defines entries with id, label, category, key combos, descriptions, and action types (navigate/callback/palette). Includes helpers for platform-aware display formatting (`formatShortcut`, `primaryShortcutDisplay`) and category grouping.\n- **Global Keyboard Shortcut Hook**: Created `lib/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` with `useKeyboardShortcuts()` hook supporting:\n  - Single key combos: `Mod+K`, `Shift+/`, etc. with cross-platform `Mod` key (Cmd on Mac, Ctrl on Windows/Linux)\n  - Two-key sequences: `G D`, `G B`, etc. (press G then D within 800ms) for SuperHuman-style navigation\n  - Automatic suppression in text inputs, textareas, contentEditable, and `.w-md-editor` elements\n  - Shift-key normalization (maps `?` back to `/` for `Shift+/` detection)\n  - `useIsMac()` helper for platform-aware display\n- **Enhanced Command Palette**: Rewrote `components/ui/CommandPalette.tsx` with:\n  - Commands auto-populated from the shortcut registry (no more hardcoded duplicates)\n  - Fuzzy search with **character-level match highlighting** (matched chars shown in primary color)\n  - Category-based sections with visual icons per category (Navigation, Kanban, Email, Meetings, Open Brain, Global)\n  - Platform-aware shortcut hints displayed per command\n  - Full ARIA support: `role=\"dialog\"`, `role=\"listbox\"`, `role=\"option\"`, `aria-activedescendant`, `aria-selected`\n  - Footer hint for `?` to open all shortcuts\n  - Callback dispatch via `palette-action` CustomEvent for actions handled by AppShell\n- **Shortcut Reference Sheet**: Created `components/ui/ShortcutReferenceSheet.tsx`:\n  - Full-screen modal with all shortcuts organized by category in a 2-column grid\n  - Platform-aware key glyph display (⌘, ⇧, ⌃, ⌥ on Mac; Ctrl, Shift, Alt on Windows)\n  - Accessible dialog with Escape to close and body scroll lock\n  - Triggered by `?` key or \"Show Keyboard Shortcuts\" in command palette\n- **Updated AppShell**: Rewrote `components/ui/AppShell.tsx` to:\n  - Wire up `useKeyboardShortcuts` hook driven by the registry\n  - Handle callback actions (theme toggle, shortcut sheet, brain capture, kanban new card)\n  - Manage state for both command palette and shortcut reference sheet\n  - Removed old inline `useEffect` keydown listeners in favor of the centralized hook\n\n### Keyboard Shortcuts Implemented\n| Category | Shortcut | Action |\n|----------|----------|--------|\n| Global | `Ctrl/⌘+K` | Toggle command palette |\n| Global | `?` (Shift+/) | Show keyboard shortcuts reference |\n| Global | `Ctrl/⌘+Shift+L` | Cycle dark/light/system theme |\n| Navigation | `Ctrl/⌘+B` | Go to Brain |\n| Navigation | `G D` | Go to Dashboard |\n| Navigation | `G B` | Go to Kanban Boards |\n| Navigation | `G I` | Go to Inbox |\n| Navigation | `G M` | Go to Meetings |\n| Navigation | `G C` | Go to Calendar |\n| Navigation | `G P` | Go to Pages |\n| Navigation | `G S` | Go to Settings |\n| Kanban | `C` | Create new card |\n| Kanban | `/` | Search cards |\n| Open Brain | `Ctrl/⌘+Shift+B` | Quick capture to Brain |\n\n### Files Modified\n- `components/ui/CommandPalette.tsx` — Rewritten with registry-driven commands, fuzzy highlighting, ARIA\n- `components/ui/AppShell.tsx` — Rewritten to use centralized shortcut hook and wire up reference sheet\n\n### Files Created\n- `lib/shortcuts/registry.ts` — Centralized shortcut registry (single source of truth)\n- `lib/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` — Global keyboard shortcut hook with sequence support\n- `components/ui/ShortcutReferenceSheet.tsx` — Full shortcut reference sheet modal\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- All shortcuts are defined in `lib/shortcuts/registry.ts` — add/remove/modify bindings there and they auto-populate both the command palette and reference sheet\n- Two-key sequences (e.g. `G D`) use an 800ms timeout window between keypresses\n- Shortcuts are automatically suppressed when focus is in inputs, textareas, contentEditable, or the markdown editor\n- The `Shift+/` → `?` mapping uses a US keyboard layout assumption via `SHIFT_KEY_MAP`\n- No new npm dependencies were added — everything is built with the existing stack\n- TypeScript compilation passes with zero errors\n- To add new shortcuts: add an entry to `SHORTCUT_REGISTRY` and, if it's a callback type, add a case to `handleCallback` in `AppShell.tsx`"
}